  "name": "Lease vs Buy Decision Analyzer",
  "nodes": [
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## \ud83c\udfe0 Lease vs Buy Decision Analyzer\n\n### What this workflow does\n1. Watches Google Drive for new lease or purchase agreement PDFs\n2. Extracts all financial terms from the new document\n3. Simultaneously extracts the comparison document (fixed file ID)\n4. Calculates 5-year total cost of ownership for both options\n5. Logs comparison results to Google Sheets\n6. Sends Slack report with recommendation and cost breakdown\n\n### Setup steps\n1. Get PDF Vector API key from pdfvector.com/api-keys\n2. Create Google Drive folder \u2014 upload documents to compare\n3. Set YOUR_COMPARISON_DOC_FILE_ID in Download Comparison node\n   (this is the other document you're comparing against)\n4. Create Google Sheet with columns:\n   Document A | Document B | Type A | Type B | 5yr Cost A | 5yr Cost B | Difference | Recommendation | Processed Date\n5. Update YOUR_FOLDER_ID, YOUR_SPREADSHEET_ID, YOUR_SLACK_CHANNEL_ID\n\n### Perfect for\n- Home buyers comparing lease vs purchase\n- Business equipment financing decisions\n- Vehicle lease vs buy analysis",
        "height": 480,
        "width": 340,
        "color": 5
      },
      "id": "a7b22729-5df2-42ac-825a-4c472ecd4100",
      "name": "Sticky Note",
